Armstrong Bakam, Bauchi No fewer than five suspects have been arrested in connection with the killing of Sunday Ezra, a security guard with New Trafford Hotels and Suites located in Gwallameji area of Bauchi metropolis, police authorities have said. The PUNCH had reported that the deceased, a 23-year old, was said to have been beaten to death over a missing small phone otherwise known as “torchlight” by persons suspected to be his co-workers. The Police Public Relations Officer, Bauchi State Command, Ahmed Wakili, confirmed the arrest of the five suspects to our correspondent in a telephone interview on Wednesday. He said that the suspects were currently in detention at the State Intelligence and Investigation Bureau at the command headquarters and were helping the police in its investigation to unravel the remote and immediate causes of the death of the late security guard. Wakili, a Deputy Superintendent of Police, explained that men of the SIIB were investigating to determine the role of every suspect arrested in connection with the offence. Copyright PUNCH.
